1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with community detection in dynamic networks, which is a subfield of social and information networks. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a new method for dynamic community detection, which can be considered as a software engineering problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents theoretical guarantees and computational complexity analysis for the proposed method, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a novel community scoring metric and compares the proposed method with baseline methods, which can be considered as a machine learning problem. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with optimizing the community structure in dynamic networks, which can be considered as a systems and control problem.
